The paper deals with optimization of spectrum sensing and accessing in a multiuser cognitive network, which involves information theory (IT) and network infrastructure (NI) aspects. The proposed framework also considers the use of multi-antenna techniques, which falls under multimedia (MM) category. The paper also discusses interference constraint, which is a security (CR) concern. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.NI, followed by cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.CR.
